item.content:
&lt;p&gt;
	An ajax site I created polls data from a separate xml database file that updates periodically. To edit it without having to modify the .xml file directly, I wrote a python class with very simple read/write functions. All it does is loop from the top of the file until it finds the tag, and then reads it or rewrites it with data given by the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;
	use&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	To read a tag:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre style=&quot;color:#000000;background:#ffffff;&quot;&gt;
xml &lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; xmlrw&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&#039;filename&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;xml&#039;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
xml&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;get_tag&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#0000e6; &quot;&gt;&#039;&amp;lt;tag&amp;gt;&#039;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; index&lt;span style=&quot;color:#808030; &quot;&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;code&gt;index&lt;/code&gt; is the number of times a tag appears starting from the top of the file (so &lt;code&gt;xmlrw.read_tag(&#039;&amp;lt;tag&amp;gt;&#039;, 2)&lt;/code&gt; would return the data between the third &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;tag&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; element).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
